\
\
6) Fixed French nib file so Typeset menu works again (there are no longer simultaneous checks on "PdfTeX" and "TeX & Ghostscript").\
\
\
7) Fixed tab settings, so now changing tab spacing in Preferences works correctly.\
\
\
8) Command-T now typesets even when the console window is active.\
\
\
9) Fixed pdf updating. If a user has an external editor and uses TeXShop to display pdf output, and if the "Automatic Preview Update" preference is set, then whenever the pdf file is updated, TeXShop reads and displays the latest version, activating the pdf window when it does so. There is a hidden preference item named "BringPdfFrontOnAutomaticUpdate". If this is set to "NO", then the preview window is supposed to be updated but not brought forward. Recently, the preview window did this, but didn't display the new content until the user manually activated it. This is fixed.\
\
10) Instead of separate commands to display each of George Gratzer's symbol tables, there is one command to display all of the tables in one document. It is much easier to find a symbol if you can scroll through tables rather than guessing which table has the desired symbol.\
\
